      <p>If you built the PDF yourself from a bunch of photos, the cleaner habit is to fix orientation at the source. Our <a href="/image-to-pdf">Image to PDF</a> tool lets you drop in your JPGs, drag them into the right reading order, and auto-fits each one to the page before you ever export. Straighten the shots there and you skip the rotate step entirely.</p>

